# luo9_sdk_cpp Build Instructions

## Prerequisites

### Windows (MinGW-w64)
- Download posix thread model MinGW-w64 from: https://github.com/niXman/mingw-builds-binaries/releases
- Choose: x86_64-*-posix-seh-ucrt version
- Extract to G:\mingw64-posix (or your preferred location)

### Windows (MSVC)
- Visual Studio 2019/2022 with C++ workload
- Or Build Tools for Visual Studio

### Linux
- GCC or Clang with C++17 support
- pthread library

## Build Commands

### Windows + MinGW-w64 (Recommended)
```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake .. -G "MinGW Makefiles" -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER="G:/mingw64-posix/bin/g++.exe"
cmake --build .
```

### Windows + MSVC (Visual Studio)
```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake .. -G "Visual Studio 16 2019" -A x64
cmake --build . --config Release
```

### Linux
```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
make -j$(nproc)
```

## Output Files

- Windows (MinGW): `build/libluo9_sdk_cpp.a`
- Windows (MSVC): `build/Release/luo9_sdk_cpp.lib`
- Linux: `build/libluo9_sdk_cpp.a`

## Install (Optional)

```bash
cmake --install . --prefix /path/to/install
```

This will install:
- Headers to `<prefix>/include/`
- Library to `<prefix>/lib/`

## GitHub Actions

Push to main branch will trigger automatic builds for:
- Windows (MinGW-w64) -> `libluo9_sdk_cpp.a`
- Windows (MSVC) -> `luo9_sdk_cpp.lib`
- Linux -> `libluo9_sdk_cpp.a`

Download artifacts from GitHub Actions page.

## Usage in Your Project

### CMake
```cmake
find_package(luo9_sdk_cpp REQUIRED)
target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE luo9_sdk_cpp)
```

### Manual
```bash
g++ -I/path/to/include your_plugin.cpp -L/path/to/lib -lluo9_sdk_cpp -o your_plugin
```

## Namespace Structure

```
luo9::
├── bus::       # Message bus (init, topic, subscribe, publish)
├── bot::       # Bot operations (get_version, send_group_msg, send_private_msg)
├── command::   # Command parsing (parse, on, on_pattern)
├── payload::   # Payload parsing (Message, MetaEvent, Notice, Request)
├── message::   # Message builder (txt, at, image, endl)
├── pattern::   # Pattern matching ({variable})
└── version::   # Version query protocol
```
